commentary: Jordan to Nasir Jamal, no run the short ball gets a wicket this time. Not yet. Jamal has reviewed it immediately. Jamal comes down the wicket to cover the movement Jordan has been drawing, Jordan drags the length short, the ball gets a bit too big on him, and it goes under his left armpit. Umpire S Ravi thinks he has gloved it, but replays show there is daylight between ball and anything else. No deviation, no sound, not even close. Overturned

commentary: Tredwell to Shafiqullah, OUT Bopara is doing everything today. Shafiq tries the big sweep, gets a big top edge that flies around deep square leg. Bopara from fine leg and Jordan from deep midwicket converge, but nobody seems to have called for this. Jordan lets it go at the last moment, and Bopara takes it with a late dive to his left. Inches off the ground
